descript.purpose: Show all monitoring stations used in the 2012 Virginia 305(b)/303(d) Water Quality Assessment Integrated Report.
descript.supplinf: This dataset is supplemental GIS data to the 2012 Virginia 305(b)/303(d) Water Quality Assessment Integrated Report, the 2012 Assessment Unit hydrology geodatabase (va_12ir_aus_all.mdb) and the regionally significant VPDES facilities shapefile (va_12ir_vpdes_facilities.shp).

idinfo.useconst: Point locations and attributes should not be altered except by the developer (VA DEQ). This dataset constitutes the EPA approved digital version of the suite of all monitoring sites used in the current water quality assessment for Virginia. Crediting the Virginia Department of Environmental Quality as data source is requested.
idinfo.datacred: This dataset was generated as a summary of monitoring sample data from many sources. Consult the 2012 Virginia 305(b)/303(d) Water Quality Assessment Integrated Report for a list of all sources considered.
idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcGIS 9.2.6.1500

procstep.procdesc: Collected each regional Microsoft Access database (ir_mon_stations_2012_<Regional Office>.mdb) to QA and ultimately merge into one statewide database.
Established multiple SQL queries to check for general errors in data entry.
Per the results of SQL QA and regional input, values were updated where necessary. Records were deleted or appended if necessary.
Compiled the completed stations table from each regional Microsoft Access database (ir_mon_stations_2012_<Regional Office>.mdb) into one statewide database.
Exported select fields from tbl_ir_mon_stations to XY point layer.

Executed Identity command to populate the VAHU61 and MAP from version 4 of the National Watershed Boundary Dataset hydrologic units layer to verify geocoding accuracy of WATERSHED and VAHU6 values entered by regional staff.
Compared the output of station location to assessment unit layers and DRGs to verify accuracy of the lat/long coordinates entered by regional staff.
Updated Access table with any revisions needed from/requested by regional staff.
Created a copy of the master database to edit for shapefile creation.
Created make table query in Access database to export a table with modified field headings to conform to dBase IV field name, type and size restrictions.
Created XY shapefile from Access table.
Added attributes needed for reporting stats and mapping purposes.
Completed dataset renamed and copied to 2012 assessment folder.
Metadata .txt file revised and imported using Metadata Import utility in ArcCatalog.

Created make table query in Access database to export a table with modified field headings to conform to dBase IV field name, type and size restrictions.
